One of the nicest parts of the whole area is STOKE FLOODS. A nature reserve managed by Warwickshire Nature Conservation Trust. The site covers an area of 19 acres, rough grassland and open water and is the home of many species of birds.
The information for this project was collected and recorded by children from three local Primary Schools. { { {CLIFFORD BRIDGE PRIMARY SCHOOL { {RICHARD LEE JUNIOR SCHOOL { {ST.BATHOLOMEW'S PRIMARY C OF E.SCHOOL}
